filtered out by the 8-word filter (primary issue)\n2. Even if it passed, the `/` vs `:` discrepancy in the actual OCR vs expected\n\nUnless... the test harness normalizes `/` → `:` in the result? Let me check if there's any normalization in the test runner. Actually, looking at the file name pattern for other files: `PIEROGI Z KAPUSTY : PIEROGI Z MIĘSEM` — that uses `:`. And looking at the generated title file format, it seems that `:` is used as the canonical multi-recipe separator in the filename.\n\nLooking at the other test files, I'm noticing a pattern: `CARAMELIZED ONION TART : VEGETARIAN VERSION` uses `:`, `HERB BAKED SALMON + DILL SAUCE VARIATION` uses `+`, and `WHOLE WHEAT BREAD WITH SEEDS : SOURDOUGH VARIATION` uses `:`. This suggests the test harness is using the filename directly as the expected output, which means the SAFFRON file's `:` in the filename should match what the algorithm produces. So either the algorithm needs to normalize `/` → `:`, or the test harness does the normalization when comparing. I'm checking the iteration 20 results more carefully now — SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK appears in the list but the entry seems to be cut off, so I need to verify whether it passed or failed in this iteration. I'm realizing the naming convention is offset—the commit labeled \"iteration 19\" is actually being tested as iteration 20. Let me check the iteration 19 results to see if SAFFRON was passing before this regression.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":888,"cache_read_input_tokens":55616,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":888},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"eb533174-fed4-4e6a-8d51-5fccd85ce376","uuid":"68d76b57-66f6-450d-b055-593d6fdea903"}
